codex
The red run exposed the intended private-GMST defect; after implementation, five of six new/strengthened tests passed. The remaining failure was a one-nanosecond TLE decimal-rounding difference, so I tightened the assertion to verify the known epoch with a one-nanosecond tolerance while keeping exact OMM verification. The Copenhagen coordinates independently recompute to `[3518304.710700, 784390.701416, 5244191.852570]`, matching the corrected fixture.
